---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Work With Me · Rack & Roster">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Work With Me</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
      <p>
        I take on a small number of independent strength gyms at a time. The work is monthly, the commitment is three months, and the point is to give you a clean line of sight into your own numbers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Who this is for</h2>
      <p>
        Owners and operators of independent strength gyms. One location or a few. You're running the business, not a regional manager reporting up to a brand. You know your floor. You know your members. What you don't have is time to build the reporting layer that would tell you which leads are actually worth paying for, which promos are actually working, and where your retention is actually breaking.
      </p>
      <p>
        If that's you, we should talk.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What the work looks like</h2>
      <p>
        Every month, I look at your numbers. Lead volume by real source. Close rates by segment. Cohort retention. Promo ROI measured on net impact, not lead count. New sales, active members, net change. Staff performance if you have a sales team.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before every call, you get a written report. Two calls a month. One mid-month to check how we're tracking, one at close to walk through what just happened and plan the next one. After every call, a written summary with action items, owners, and deadlines. Between calls, you can email me. I respond in real time.
      </p>
      <p>
        When your data is broken at the source, whether that's tagging, source buckets, or what you're capturing at lead entry, I tell you how to fix it. I write the spec. You or your staff implement.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What I need to start</h2>
      <p>
        Three exports from your POS or CRM: six months of leads, six months of sales, and your current roster including recent cancels. Don't worry about the format. Whatever your system gives you, I'll work with.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The offer</h2>
      <p>
        $1,000 a month. Three-month minimum. At the end, we decide together whether to continue.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm taking on a few clients this year. If you're one of them, email me at <a href="mailto:stephen@rackandroster.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-neutral-600">stephen@rackandroster.com</a> and tell me about your gym.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
